Compared to the colorful, animated interfaces that students use every day, the text-only output of a typical CS1 Python program is neither exciting, engaging nor motivating. But incorporating graphical output into a CS1 assignment can be tedious and time-consuming for an instructor and challenging for students. As a solution, this poster presents an Easy Graphical Asset (EGA) that provides a ready-to-use mechanism for defining and animating the movement of a graphical element along a linear path. The asset is composed of 3 customizable elements: a background image, a divided linear path